\section{Abrahamic Covenant}
\label{sec:abrahamicCovenant}

\subsection{The Covenant}

\begin{enumerate}
 \item ``I will make of thee a great nation'' (Abr. 2:9)
 \item ``thou shalt be a blessing unto thy seed after thee, that in their
hands they shall bear this ministry and Priesthood unto all nations'' (Abr. 2:9)
\item ``in thy seed after thee$\ldots$shall all the families of the earth be
blessed, even with the blessings of the Gospel, which are the blessings of
salvation, even of
life eternal.'' (Abr. 2:11)
\end{enumerate}

\subsection{What does it mean?}

\begin{enumerate}
 \item I am a part of a ``great nation'' of believers.
 \item I hold the priesthood, and further, I served a mission in which I
``bore'' the priesthood to others.
 \item I have the gospel, and further, I served a mission in which I brought
the gospel to others.  Another thought is, as mentioned by Elder McConkie later
in these notes, this has to do with eternal families. {\it Note:} in some way
it will be to our salvation to be linked as a large eternal family.
\end{enumerate}

\

Another thought: patriarchal blessing.

\

There is something in God making a special covenant with Abraham.
He must honor that covenant. (Although, note that He wouldn't make a covenant
He didn't wish to make.)  Where are all the places where God makes a special
covenant with people?  How can we receive a ``special covenant''?

\subsection{Historical Timeline}

\begin{itemize}
 \item The covenant started with Abraham, was passed down to Isaac, then Jacob
(i.e. Israel), then Joseph.
\item Moses freed Israel from Egyptian bondage
\item Israel split into two: Ephraim (or Israel) in the north and Judah in the
south
\item 721 B.C. Ephraim is taken by the Assyrians and lost
\item Christ comes through Judah
\begin{itemize}
 \item Gen 49.10
 \item Gen TJS 50:24
\end{itemize}
\item Today we are the ones who have the Abrahamic covenant: 3. Ne. 25-26
We need to do missionary work to gather those of ``Israel''.
\item In the last days there will be two cities
\begin{itemize}
 \item New Jerusalem (Ether 13:3-6, D\&C 84:1-5)
\item Jerusalem
\end{itemize}
\end{itemize}


\subsection{Millennium}

Handout: ``O Youth of the Noble Birthright''

Ten tribes to return during the Millennium (Millenial Messiah p. 251).
Physical return to Palestine (Millenial Messiah p. 319-321; also note on A of F
10).


\subsection{Malachi 4:5-6}

\begin{quote}
 Mal 4:5-6: Elijah to return to ``turn the heart of the fathers to
the children, and the heart of the children to their fathers''.
\end{quote}

\begin{quote}
Moroni (to Joseph Smith): ``And he shall plant in the hearts of the children the
promises made to the fathers, and the hearts of the children shall turn to their
fathers. If it were not so, the whole earth would be utterly wasted at his
coming.''
\end{quote}

\begin{quote}
Bruce R. McConkie: ``Both of these translations are correct$\ldots$Taken
together,
they give us an expanded and comprehensive view of the mission of Elijah that we
would not gain from either of them alone.'' (The Millenial Messiah, p. 266)
\end{quote}

\begin{quote}
Joseph Smith: ``He shall reveal the covenants of the fathers in relation to the
children, and the covenants of the children in relation to the fathers.''
(Teachings, p. 321)
\end{quote}

\begin{quote}
Bruce R. McConkie: ``Who are the fathers?  They are Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob,
to
whom the promises were made.  What are the promises?  They are the promises of a
continuation of the family unit in eternity; of posterity in numbers as the dust
of the earth and the stars in the firmament; of eternal increase; and of the
consequent glory, and honor, and exaltation, and eternal life inherent in such a
way of eternal existence.''
\end{quote}

\subsection{Land of Canaan}
\label{sub:landOfCanaan}

\begin{quote}
 God gave ancient Canaan to Abraham, Isaac and Jacob, and the twelve tribes of
Israel, of whom the Ten Tribes are the dominant part.  It is their land, in time
and eternity.  It is their land now whenever they are worthy to tread its
blessed surface.  And it shall be theirs again in that everlasting eternity that
lies ahead.
Bruce R. McConkie, \textit{The Millenial Messiah}, p. 322
\end{quote}

\begin{quote}
The President of the Church is the only person on earth at any
given time who does or can exercise these [meaning the keys of the gathering of
Israel and the restoration of the ten tribes] or any other priesthood keys in
their eternal fulness.  He will direct the return of the Ten Tribes.  It will
not come to pass in any other way.
  Bruce R. McConkie, \textit{The Millenial Messiah}, p. 323
\end{quote}

\begin{quote}
 ``$\ldots$the great day of the return of the Ten Tribes, the day when the
assembling
hosts shall fulfill the prophetic promises, shall come after the Lord's
return.'' (Also from Bruce R. McConkie, \textit{The Millenial Messiah}, p. 323,
I think.)
\end{quote}

