\section{Creation}

\subsection{Differences between the Creation Accounts}

\begin{itemize}
 \item Genesis: sparse; Moses: God introduces it and speaks in the first person;
Abraham: plural
 \item Abraham: the darkness was because there was nothing on the earth yet
 \item Abraham: they ``comprehended'' the light
 \item Moses: God called light day and darkness night ``by the power of His
word''; Abraham is more specific in what is day and what is night
 \item Abraham: ``expanse'' in the midst of the waters; Moses: ``it was so,
even as
I spake''
 \item Abraham: the Gods ``organized the earth to bring forth grass''
Moses: specifies the greater light is the sun, and the lesser is the moon
 \item Abraham: the Gods counseled
 \item $\ldots$ Moses: everything was created spiritually
 \item Abraham omits a seemingly unimportant piece
 \item Moses: free to choose
 \item Abraham: time of Kolob
 \item Moses: God breathed into the animals the breathe of life
 \item Abraham puts the creation of Eve in a different spot
\end{itemize}

