\subsection{Faith and Fear}

Can't have both faith and fear simultaneously.

{\it Example:} Peter walks on water, but then begins to fear.

\subsection{Faith and Confidence}

I read a blog post (Gordon Bean) about faith and confidence.  Here are some of the
points I learned from it:

\begin{itemize}
	\item Confidence is a consequence of faith.  We do not choose to
		have confidence, but is a consequence of our knowledge.  For
		example, if I have a phone in my hand, I cannot make myself be
		confident that when I release my hand it will not fall to the
		ground.
	\item Faith is about accepting light and truth when we encounter
		it and following it.
\end{itemize}

