\subsection{My personal opinion}

\textit{from when I was single}

I feel in my heart that I am doing OK in dating. I may not date up to my
own---unrealistic?---expectations, but I am doing what I can. Procuring dates is
a
weakness for me, so I believe that I cannot be expected to do as well as others
at it.

	Some say that if a man doesn't make temple marriage happen, then he
automatically falls short of exaltation. My feeling is, if I live a righteous
life I will have that opportunity, whether I achieve it in this life or not. I
will not be guaranteed that opportunity, however, if I decide to marry outside
of the covenant instead of holding out for more. In my opinion that is the
separator.

