\subsection{Judas and Agency}

He had agency, and if he didn't betray Christ, Christ would've been killed in
some other way; further, he helped the Jews sin in that they murdered an
innocent man

\begin{itemize}
 \item  \textit{Doctrines of Salvation} 1:61: "Judas had his agency and acted
upon it; no pressure was brought to bear on him to cause him to betray the Lord,
but he was led by Lucifer"
 \item TJS p. 67: Judas was apostate
 \item Luke 22:3 Satan entered into Judas
 \item \textit{The Mortal Messiah} 4:15-18: Explanation of Judas' possible
motives
\end{itemize}

