1978,
3
\begin{quote}
Certainly. There can be no question about this. If they gain salvation, which is
eternal life, which is exaltation, it means that they are married and live in
the family unit. President Joseph Fielding Smith has so stated in plain words,
and it is something that must necessarily be so. (See Doctrines of Salvation,
2:49-57.)
\end{quote}

