 \subitem Elder
 \subitem High Priest
 \subitem Patriarch
 \subitem Seventy
 \subitem Apostle
\end{itemize}

\noindent Handout: ``Three Types of Revealed Church Government''.
A summary of this handout is as follows.  In the beginning, the church was built
upon a patriarchal system, where the next in the patriarchal line was chosen to
be the prophet.  In the middle, the church was on a many prophets system.  God
called prophets directly to complete missions.  Finally, the church is organized
in its current form.

\subsection{The Patriarchal Order}

Note that the birthright was different from the right to lead the church.  For
example Esau sells Isaac his birthright, but then that is different from the
blessing he received which was supposed to be Esau's.

