\subsection{Role of the Prophet in Different Eras}

I have a question about the role of the prophet in different eras.
I already know that in different eras the prophet has been a
different responsibility.  I am thinking about the difference when a
prophet is in charge of a church and not, and when a prophet brings
forth scripture and not.

I know however that the prophet today is called to lead the church
and is inspired of the Lord.

\subsection{Personal Experiences}

\begin{itemize}
 \item Basic things: Word of Wisdom, Law of Chastity, Law of Tithing
 \item 2 Tim. 1:7-8: Gordon B. Hinckley suggested that we read it every day; as
I have done that I have felt strength in remembering that "God hath not given us
the spirit of fear" and to not be "ashamed of the testimony of our Lord."
 \item Following local leaders:
Bishop told us to dedicate our homes; as I left my apartment, which I had
dedicated, I felt a great sense that God had protected and watched over me
there, and that part of this was through dedicating my home.
 \item Bishop told us to go to dance; I wouldn't have otherwise gone; I received
such confidence and power from that experience; even though I didn't marry the
girl I asked to the dance---or even go on another date with her---I was able to
get out on more dates in the months that followed than I normally would have
gone on.
\end{itemize}

