``How to Give a Good Talk'', Missionary Journal
\begin{quote}

Have ``meat''

Prepare in advance

Prepare thoroughly so that you gain the ability to speak on the subject by the
spirit

Cut out the fluff

Give something which is not obvious

Clarity

Focus on main points

Use steps

Cut out the fluff---use direct language

Interest

Use a good hook

Deliver it with confidence

Cut out the fluff---get to the point

Stories are good

Visual aids are good

When appropriate, participation is good


