\vspace{1 em}

\noindent Example of former BYU star who turned down NFL:
His name is Eli Herring.  A quick search turns up articles about him.  It is an
intriguing choice and something I can support because I know that as a result he
gets an easier and more spiritually-enriched life.

\vspace{1 em}

Elder Bruce R. McConkie taught that ``Sabbath observance was a sign between
ancient Israel and their God whereby the chosen people might be
known.''\footnote{Bruce R. McConkie, \it{Mormon Doctrine}, 2nd ed. [1966], 658;
see also Neh. 13:15–22; Isa. 56:1–8; Jer. 17:19–27; Ezek. 46:1–7; Ex. 31:12–17.}

President Gordon B. Hinckley expressed concern that members of the Church may
have a tendency to take on the ways of the world. He said: ``We don't adopt them
immediately, but we slowly take them on, unfortunately. I wish I had the power
to convert this whole Church to the observance of the Sabbath. I know our people
would be more richly blessed of the Lord if they would walk in faithfulness in
the observance of the Sabbath.''\footnote{Heber City/Springville Utah regional
conference, priesthood leadership meeting, 13 May 1995.}

